# Git first (step 0)

Before making **code or resource** changes in this workspace, ensure **`main`** (or the active branch) is current with **`origin`**: run **`git pull`** (or fetch + merge/rebase as the owner prefers) so local work matches GitHub. The owner uses **multiple machines**; skipping pull causes duplicate effort, merge pain, and “the other Cursor had the project but not the fix” drift.

If **`git pull`** reports conflicts, resolve them **before** new edits. Shell-capable agents should **`git pull`** at session start when the task touches the repo.
